The paper discusses cooperative multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL) which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on coordination and scalability suggests that it may also fall under the categories of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the mention of non-stationarity suggests that it may also be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
